 Joe Mesmar is a professional, dynamic, and innovative DJ and music producer based out of Montreal, Canada. He started his career at just 19 years of age, and now at 21, Mesmar boasts three EP's to his name, with 3 more to be released this year.As his credits continue to grow and he carries on performing on local and national stages,
 Mesmar's name is set to climb the charts and his notoriety continues to swell.Mesmar's style includes: Tech House, Deep House, and Techno. He spins and produces music influenced by Gary Beck, Chris Liebing, Sasha Carassi (his favorite), Filterheadz, Monoloc, Adam Bayer and many more. His cutting-edge tracks feature a vibrant, unique energy and passion that can be found nowhere else.
 His flawless mixes are often unexpected, original combinations that inspire and entertain audiences of all ages and musical preferences.
 Joe Mesmar got his start on YouTube where his fan base grew exponentially in a short time. With a demand for more music and live performances, Mesmar's fans have supported him in creating a true phenomenon.
 Recent notable performances include spinning at Drip 'N Play in Montreal, Canada and at the Beach Party Festival in New York. Mesmar's track, "Worth It", reached the #1 spot on Spinnin' Records and remained there for three weeks followed by a two week stint at #2. Other tracks receive critical acclaim and accolades.
 Mesmar studies programming and computer science while creating techno compilations that he publishes online and brings to the studio for future release on EP's. For fun, when he's not in the studio, Mesmar enjoys sports, specifically basketball, swimming, and exercising in general. He feels as though he was born to produce music and is most proud of his most recent productions to be released in 2013.
